President Biden has declared a major disaster in the State of Alaska due to a severe storm, flooding, and landslides that occurred from September 15 to September 20, 2022. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The declaration provides funding for individuals in the Regional Educational Attendance Areas of Bering Strait, Kashunamiut, Lower Kuskokwim, and Lower Yukon. Assistance can include grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other programs to aid in recovery. Federal funding is also available for emergency protective measures and hazard mitigation statewide. Timothy B. Manner has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Damage assessments are ongoing, and additional areas and forms of assistance may be designated once assessments are completed. Residents and business owners in the designated areas can apply for assistance through DisasterAssistance.gov or by calling FEMA. Further information can be obtained by contacting the FEMA News Desk.